explanation: This solution uses a stack to keep track of the current formula being processed. It iterates through the formula, and whenever it encounters a '(', it pushes a new dictionary onto the stack. Whenever it encounters a ')', it pops the top dictionary off the stack and updates the counts of the elements in the current formula. The solution also handles the case where the count of an element is greater than 1. Finally, it constructs the output string by iterating through the elements in the stack and appending their names and counts to the string.

